=> Looking if colors are close:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Color_difference#CIEDE2000
use the https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CIELAB_color_space
L* for the lightness from black (0) to white (100), a* from green (-) to red (+), and b* from blue (-) to yellow (+)

* Ruby gems
- https://github.com/halostatue/color
RGB, CMYK, HSL
A technique for generating monochromatic contrasting palettes is also included.

- https://rubygems.org/gems/color-rgb/versions/0.0.2
  https://github.com/apartmenttherapy/color-rgb
RGB color utilities for converting RGB color into different colorspace
(CIE*Lab or XYZ), a different format, or comparing similarity of two colors

